Wieloręki bandyta¶

Praca domowa nr 1 - Reinforcement learning (10-ręki bandyta)¶

Zadanie - problem wielorękiego bandyty¶

Zreprodukuj obrazek 2.3 ze strony 34 "Reinforcement Learning: An Introduction" Sutton, Barto. Czyli:

Estymuj wartość średnią bandyty przy pomocy wzoru Q_{n+1} = Q_n + alpha_n* (R_n - Q_n), gdzie alpha = 0.1. Porównaj 2 podejścia:

  1. eps-greedy epsilon = 0.1 , gdzie Q_1=0.
  2. greedy gdzie Q_1=5. Narysuj wykres 2D, gdzie na osi OX będzie liczba gier, a na osi OY % wyborów najlepszego bandyty.

Mamy 10 bandytów:

  1. N(0.1,1) 2-10. N(0,1)
In [19]:
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
import random
In [20]:
#Generating rewards for the bandits, determining the parameters
def RewardDrawing(i):
    if i==0:
        return np.random.normal(0.1, 1)
    else:
        return np.random.normal(0,1)
    
iter=10000 #nr of iterations, there are 1000 in the book, but I wanted to see how it looks for more iterations
N_greedy = [0 for _ in range(10)] #nr of selections for each of the bandits by the greedy agent
N_eps_greedy = [0 for _ in range(10)] #Number of selections for each of the bandits by the eps_greedy agent
Q_eps_greedy = [0 for _ in range(10)] 
Q_greedy = [5 for _ in range(10)]
epsilon=0.1
alpha=0.1
optimal_bandit=0 #highest expected reward
optimal_percentage_eps_greedy=[0 for _ in range(iter)] #(nr of the best bandit selections)/(nr of all selections)*100% by the eps_greedy agent
optimal_percentage_greedy=[0 for _ in range(iter)] #(nr of the best bandit selections)/(nr of all selections)*100% by the greedy agent
In [21]:
#eps_greedy
for i in range(iter):
    if random.random() < epsilon:
        bandit = random.randint(0,9)
    else:
        bandit =  random.choice([i for i, x in enumerate(Q_eps_greedy) if x == max(Q_eps_greedy)])
        
    reward = RewardDrawing(bandit)
    N_eps_greedy[bandit] += 1
    Q_eps_greedy[bandit] += (reward-Q_eps_greedy[bandit])*alpha
    optimal_percentage_eps_greedy[i] = N_eps_greedy[optimal_bandit]/(i+1)*100
#greedy
for j in range(iter):
    bandit = random.choice([i for i, x in enumerate(Q_greedy) if x == max(Q_greedy)])

    reward = RewardDrawing(bandit)
    N_greedy[bandit] += 1
    Q_greedy[bandit] += (reward-Q_greedy[bandit])*alpha
    optimal_percentage_greedy[j] = N_greedy[optimal_bandit]/(j+1)*100
